title: Woman finds ‘demon’ staring at her after Snapchat selfie | Daily Mail Online
text: comments A woman in search of the perfect Snapchat selfie could not believe her eyes when she took a snap and found a 'demon' glaring back at her. Rachael Gardiner, 22, from East Kilbride, in Scotland, used a filter that was supposed to cover her face with a wreath of purple flowers. However, when she glanced back at the photo she found a sinister face staring into the camera from just below her chin. Rachael Gardiner (left) used a filter to take a selfie and found a sinister face staring into the camera from just below her chin (right) RELATED ARTICLES
